.TH JATAI 1 "2026-03-23" "0.6.5" "Jataí Manual"
.SH NAME
jatai \- local file-system message bus for scripts and agents
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B jatai
[\fICOMMAND\fR] [\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\fIARGS\fR]
.br
.B jatai
[\fIPATH\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B Jataí
is a local micro-email and messaging bus that routes files between nodes on the
file system. Each node is a directory containing an INBOX and an OUTBOX. Files
dropped into an OUTBOX are delivered to the INBOXes of all registered nodes.
The background daemon watches for new files and handles delivery, retries, and
error reporting via filename prefix conventions.
.PP
Invoking
.B jatai
with no arguments displays this help summary. The interactive TUI is not yet
available and will replace this behaviour in a future release.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B jatai [\fIPATH\fR]
Shorthand for \fBjatai init\fR \fIPATH\fR. When \fIPATH\fR is provided and is
not a known sub-command, the directory at \fIPATH\fR is initialised as a new
Jataí node.
.TP
.B jatai init [\fIPATH\fR]
Initialise a Jataí node at \fIPATH\fR (defaults to the current working
directory). Creates the INBOX and OUTBOX directories, writes a local
\fI.jatai\fR configuration file, and registers the node in the global
registry at \fI~/.jatai\fR.
.TP
.B jatai status
Show the status of the Jataí node in the current directory: INBOX and OUTBOX
file counts.
.TP
.B jatai start
Start the Jataí background daemon. The daemon watches all registered node
OUTBOXes and delivers files to their destination INBOXes. Auto-start is
registered for the current login session.
.TP
.B jatai stop
Stop the running Jataí daemon.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.jatai
Global registry and configuration file (YAML).
.TP
.I ~/.jatai.pid
PID file written by the daemon while it is running.
.TP
.I ~/.jatai.log
Log file produced by the daemon.
.TP
.I ~/.retry
Persistent retry-state file (JSON) tracking exponential back-off counters.
.TP
.I <NODE>/.jatai
Local node configuration file (YAML). Overrides global defaults for that node.
.TP
.I <NODE>/._jatai
Soft-delete marker. When present the node is considered disabled without
removing its configuration.
.TP
.I <NODE>/.jatai.bkp
Automatic backup of the previous local configuration, used for rollback when a
configuration change causes a prefix collision.
.SH FILE PREFIX CONVENTIONS
Jataí uses filename prefixes to encode delivery state:
.TP
.B (no prefix)
File is pending delivery.
.TP
.B _
File was delivered successfully (processed).
.TP
.B !
Partial or total error \(em delivery failed after all retries.
.TP
.B !!
Fatal error \(em unrecoverable delivery failure.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B JATAI_REGISTRY
Override the default path to the global registry file (not yet implemented).
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Operational error (node not found, daemon already running, etc.).
.SH BUGS
Report bugs at \fIhttps://github.com/zvorky/jatai/issues\fR
